tags.note: A day-use fee of $2 USD is levied to enter the park, payable at a pay station at Kelton Avenue.

tags.description: Oakland Park is an Army Corps of Engineers park. The service at the main gate of the park is wonderful and the grounds seem to be clean and well kept. Oakland Park is connected to West Lake Park and the entry fee gets you access to both parks.
tags.name: Oakland Park
tags.note: $4 per vehicle, day use. Boat Ramp Fee is Included with entry fee of $4

tags.description: Westlake Park a huge park with amazing views of Lake Lewisville and the Lake Lewisville bridge. There is plenty to do in this park including swimming, fishing, and relaxing. This park is also connected to beautiful Oakland Park and the $4 entry fee gets
tags.name: Westlake Park
tags.note: Fees: $4 per vehicle ($1 per person walk-up)

tags.description: This park is the only Town owned park in Hickory Creek and is located at the corner of Tanglewood and Robins Nest inside of Lakewood Gardens Subdivision (just off east Main Street). This park has a playground with swings, slides and picnic tables, benches
tags.name: Tanglewood Community Park

tags.description: This park has a beautiful playground area with picnic tables and benches and lots of privacy. This park has no access to boat ramps.
tags.name: Harbor Lane Park
